				<h2>Background</h2>
			</header>
			<section>
				<header>
					<h3><strong>DealTapp</strong></h3>
					<p>Connecting users with local businesses</p>
				</header>
				<div class="8u 12u$(medium)">
					<p>DealTapp is an app that lets users find the best deals at local restaurants, cafes, and entertainment venues. It gives power to small and local shops while making it easy for users to claim the offers.</p>
				</div>
					<div class="8u 12u$(medium)">
						<p>I am the sole designer at DealTapp. This puts a lot of responsibility on my shoulders. From shaping the user experience to discussing business goals with the founders, I have a hand in every aspect of the company's success.</p>
					</div>
			</section>

 			<header class="major special">
				<h2>Testing the Interface</h2>
			</header>
			<section>
				<header>
					<h3><strong>User Testing</strong></h3>
				</header>
				<div class="8u 12u$(medium)">
					<p>To maximize budget and minimize redundancy, I started out by testing 5 users as recommended by <a href="https://www.nngroup.com/articles/why-you-only-need-to-test-with-5-users/" class="inline-link">Jakob Nielsen</a>.</p>
					<p>Testing users revealed many points of confusion. I prioritized these into the main set of issues.</p>
					<ul>
						<li>The overall purpose of the app was not clear enough.</li>
						<li>The location of the sign up/sign in feature was not intuitive.</li>
						<li>What to do after claiming a deal.</li>
						<li>The menu icon was not conventional and only accessible from the home page.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="8u 12u$(medium)">
					<p>Now that I have a list of problems; I need to build solutions.</p>
				</div>
			</section>

